[node name="HelpText" type="Label" parent="TerminalVBox" unique_id=1544330945]
layout_mode = 2
size_flags_vertical = 1
text = "Terminal Commands:
KILL - Disables mechanical signals like cameras. Doesn't work on guards.
RUN - Runs a specific hack program. For this tutorial, the only hack is DECRYPT. Use it against Signals that are encrypted.
OP - Does a contextual action based on the signal type. For example, toggles lock/unlock on doors, activates distractions.
More commands will be unlocked further into the game!

Syntax:
-Typing a command by itself uses that command on the current session. For example, if you're connected to the cam_01 session, KILL will target cam_01.
- You can also specify a target for KILL, which will automatically switch to that session and execute the command. For example, if you type KILL cam_01 from anywhere.
[JUST KIDDING SPECIFYING A TARGET DOESN\"T WORK CORRECTLY RIGHT NOW.]
 
Notes:
- Terminal commands are not case sensitive.

Press F1 to close this and resume the game."

